NV PhilipsGloeilampenfabrieken &lt;PGLO.AS> shares are due to start tradingon the New York Stock Exchange on April 14, Philips chairmanCor van der Klugt told the annual shareholders meeting.    In March, the Dutch electronics group announced it wouldend its current over the counter listing on the New York NASDAQsystem and move to the NYSE.    Philips said the "big board" listing in New York is expectedto boost its profile in the U.S., Where 10 pct of alloutstanding Philips shares are held. Reuter&#3;